    <section style="margin-bottom:2rem">
      <h2>The Mindset Shift: From Doer to Director</h2>
      <p>The most successful solo founders using AI automation describe a fundamental shift in how they think about their role. They stopped thinking of themselves as the person who does the work. They became the person who <em>directs</em> the work.</p>
      <p>This requires a different skill set: writing clear prompts (like writing clear briefs for employees), reviewing AI output critically, and knowing which decisions require human judgment versus which can be delegated to automation.</p>
      <p>The founders who fail with AI automation are the ones who try to micromanage every output. The ones who succeed set clear objectives, trust the system to execute, and spend their time on the decisions only they can make: customer relationships, strategic direction, and product vision.</p>
    </section>

